# Go!Â Retail

Go!Â RetailÂ Group is a family of brandsÂ comprisedÂ ofÂ Toys Râ€™ US,Â Calendars.com , Calendar Club, andÂ Go! Toys & Games, Attic Salt, NIQUEA. D,Â Snoozimals, Tiny Headed Kingdom, andÂ Kobioto. Since 1993, we have successfullyÂ operatedÂ the largest fleet of pop-up stores in the world, with operations in six countries.

Website:Â  [Go!Retail Group](https://goretailgroup.com/)

# The Scope

This project will only be for Go! Calendar, Toys and Games. This will be a 50% split across the stores for a 2 month A/B test. This business is valued at $120M in revenue. They have 620 stores today, but 450 of them are seasonal and are only open from August-January. Stores may change locations and format from year to year. 75% of them are franchised stores.

anuary. Stores may change locations and format from year to year. 75% of them are franchised stores.

- Locations probably stay in the same city and even in the same shopping mall, but one year it might be in a great location by the food court and the next year it might be at the end of the mall near a low-performing anchor store. These changes can mean very different sales.
- Short leases are negotiated in malls to determine success and scalability which is dependent on space availability
- Formats might change from a kiosk to a small store to a larger store
- Allocation today is very manual using mainly excel and a home-grown system. The planners spend a lot of time creating priorities and grading stores.

- Have some data already today and provided a store split for 2023 season based on 2022 data for confidence

- In season, allocations/replenishment are performed daily.
- They are a mix of franchise and corporate stores. About 15% are corporate owned.
- They are able to store most inventory in the off-season or move to their year-round stores. Products are not new every year. The exception is calendars. For calendars, the vendor takes back what they donâ€™t sell for most of the products.

If dc_dos is greater than 180, or if dc_dos is four times larger than dc_dos_next and exceeds 90, it is flagged as exclude = 0 (add_back). The reason for keeping these pairs as add_back is to enable the distribution of these products to stores, as their high stock levels in the warehouse might be due to situations such as being new products.
